<font color="#FF0000">TO ERNEST</font><br>
<tt>Sun May 25 12:52:37 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
Ernest,<br><br>
I have heard your feelings expressed by others.<br><br>
All I can say is that in 1969, when I received my orders for Vietnam, I would have gladly traded places. <br><br>
My advice to you is to not look back, understand that each person's contribution is important, and rejoice that you knew the men of whom you speak - the one's who fell.<br><br>
Peace to you.
<p><code>-- wingman@greene.xtn.net  (Tom Dier) </code><p>


